goals.question: What is the distribution of daily trading volumes?

goals.question: What is the relationship between the daily trading volume and the difference between the high and low prices?

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['open'] = pd.to_numeric(data['open'], errors='coerce')
    plt.hist(data['open'], bins=50, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['open'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['open'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['open'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['open'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("What is the distribution of daily opening prices?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='date')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['close'])
    plt.title('What is the trend of the closing prices over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    plt.scatter(data['open'], data['close'])
    plt.title('What is the relationship between the opening and closing prices?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Open')
    plt.ylabel('Close')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of daily trading volumes?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    plt.scatter(data['difference'], data['volume'], alpha=0.5)
